com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.embedded

Class EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.embedded.EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICatalysServerLifecycleListener

    public final class EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapter
extends Object
implements ICatalysServerLifecycleListener
    This class is used to wrap a Catalys Server instance with a messaging and event interface.

    The embedding application supplies a IFIXListenerProviderCallback. When the Catalys Server message processor needs a listener to deliver either a session status event or an inbound FIX message it calls back to the embedding application which is expected to supply the listener. It is up to the embedding application whether a separate listener is supplied per ID or whether the same listener is supplied for all IDs.

    By default the Catalys Server tries to reuse inbound message objects to achieve the best possible performance. However, if the embedding application prefers to receive a new message object for each inbound FIX message then it must provide a IStatefulFIXListenerCallback instance on invocation of IFIXListenerProviderCallback.getListener(String). The implementing class then has the ability to specify that it would like to receive a new message instance each time via IStatefulFIXListenerCallback.storesMessages().

    It is strongly recommended that listener callback implementations do not block otherwise the internal operations of the Catalys Server may be affected. If this cannot be guaranteed then it is recommended to process incoming events and messages in a separate thread, with an appropriate buffer of some kind inserted in between the delivery and processing threads.

    The embedding application may send messages in one of two ways:

    1. Via the send(String, IFIXMessage) method which performs a IFIXSourceProxy lookup by message processor ID on the fly.
    2. By maintaining a reference to a named IFIXSourceProxy and calling its IFIXSourceProxy.fireMessage(IFIXMessage) method directly. This avoids the cost of a lookup on each message send.

    The embedding application must always be prepared to handle errors when attempting to send FIX messages. It is possible to check beforehand whether a particular IFIXSourceProxy is logged on (via IFIXSourceProxy.isLoggedOn()), however, relying on this to guarantee a message will be sent (or not) is not adequate since it is always possible for the state of a FIX session to change between calls. Specifically, sometimes low level networking errors are not detected until an attempt to send a message is made. Always code defensively - expect and handle errors when sending FIX messages.

      • EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapter

        public EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapter(String[] args,
                                  Map<String,IFIXListenerCallback> listeners)
        Deprecated. Use EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapter(String[], IFIXListenerProviderCallback) instead.
        Constructor.

        The caller must use start() to start the embedded Catalys Server.

        Parameters:
        args - The Catalys Server's command line arguments.
        listeners - The listeners and their associated EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapterProcessor IDs. The listeners are automatically registered and de-registered with the appropriate EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapterProcessor implementations at the correct points in the component life-cycle. Each ID specified must correspond to a configured EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapterProcessor instance and there must be a listener registered for every EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapterProcessor instance. Failure to meet both of these requirements will result in the application failing to start.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - On listener specification error.

      • initializeLoggingSubsystem

        public static void initializeLoggingSubsystem()
        Initialize the logging subsystem.

        If the embedding application wishes to use configured Catalys Server based logging and it creates any loggers via the LoggerManager prior to loading this class then this method must be called beforehand.

        If no loggers are created prior to loading this class then this method need not be called and Catalys Server logging is enabled by default.

      • getFIXSourceProxy

        public IFIXSourceProxy getFIXSourceProxy(String id)
        Return the underlying FIX source proxy with the specified ID.

        The FIX source listener proxy is backed by a Catalys Server message processor and may be used to directly send messages to FIX via FIX sessions in which the underlying message is configured.

        Clients may use this method as an alternative to send(String, IFIXMessage) to avoid ID based component lookups.

        Parameters:
        id - The FIX source proxy ID.
        Returns:
        The FIX source proxy, or null if no such proxy exists.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - When no proxy exists with the specified id.

      • send

        public void send(String id,
                 IFIXMessage message)
          throws Exception
        Send a message to FIX.

        This method looks up the underlying IFIXSourceProxy associated with the specified ID on each call. Consider caching the underlying IFIXSourceProxy via getFIXSourceProxy(String) to avoid this lookup.

        Parameters:
        id - The ID of the proxy via which to send the message.
        message - The message to send.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - When no proxy exists with the specified id.
        Exception - On underlying send error.
        See Also:
        IFIXSource.fireMessage(IFIXMessage)
